	 * `attacker` against `defender`: granted when another living combatant
	 * (not the attacker or defender themselves) occupies a grid square on the
	 * straight line between them, per the "Cover" rules — one creature
	 * providing cover for another. Simplified to this one case: this app
	 * doesn't model terrain/objects as separate obstacles from walls (which
	 * already fully block a shot via hasLineOfSight() instead of granting
	 * partial cover), so Three-Quarters Cover and wall-corner Half Cover
	 * aren't modeled. Returns 0 without a grid (e.g. the unit tests' bare
	 * combatant fixtures) or if attacker/defender aren't at least 2 squares
	 * apart (nothing can stand between adjacent combatants).
